Class ExplicitMethod

java.lang.Object
  com.luigisgro.cqf.fdm.ExplicitMethod
All Implemented Interfaces:
FiniteDifferenceModel
Direct Known Subclasses:
ExplicitMethodConstantVolatility, ExplicitMethodUncertainVolatility
public abstract class ExplicitMethod
extends java.lang.Object
implements FiniteDifferenceModel

Implementation of the Explicit method for Finite Difference Method. It performs calculation of partial derivatives, and return the value of the next time step, using the three grid point in the previous time step, and the stock boundary value at the highest and lowest stock step index

Author:
Luigi Sgro

                             double delta,

Calculates the theta of the instrument. This method is abstract since it will be implemented in a different way in constant volatility method and uncertain volatility method.

Parameters:
s - The value of the stock
value - The value of the grid at the point of calculation
delta - The value of delta at the point of calculation
gamma - The value of gamma at the point of calculation
r - The interest rate
Returns:
The approximated partial derivative with respect to time
